13 SECTION 2. Subsection (d)(2) of section 87B of said chapter 112, as so appearing, is
14 hereby amended by striking out clauses (A) and (B), in lines 35-43, and inserting in place thereof
15 the following clauses:-
16 (A) is certified or licensed in the other state and is in good standing in the other state;
17 (B) has passed the Uniform Certified Public Accountant Examination and has completed
18 the education requirements listed in subsection (e) of section 87A1/2; or
19 SECTION 3. Said section 87B is hereby further amended by striking out subsection
20 (h)(2), and inserting in place thereof the following subsection:-
21 (h)(2) A person whose principal place of business is outside the commonwealth shall be
22 deemed to have qualifications substantially equivalent to the commonwealth's requirements for
23 the practice of public accountancy and shall be authorized to engage in the practice of certified
24 public accountancy in the commonwealth, including offering and rendering professional
25 services, whether in person or by mail, telephone or electronic means, if such person holds: (i) a
26 valid license as a certified public accountant issued by any other state: provided that the
27 individual has met the education and experience requirements listed in subsection (e) of 87A1/2
28 and has passed the Uniform Certified Public Accountant Examination or exceed the licensure
29 requirements of this chapter or approved by the board. Notwithstanding any other provision of
30 law, no notice or other submission shall be required by any individual who offers or renders
31 professional services under this section, whether in person or by mail, telephone, or electronic
32 means. An individual who practices in this state pursuant to this section consents, as a condition
33 of the grant of such practice privilege: to the personal and subject matter jurisdiction and
34 disciplinary authority of the board; to comply with this section and the board’s rules; that in the
