35 event the individual’s license from the other state is no longer valid, the individual will cease
36 offering or rendering professional services in the commonwealth individually or on behalf of a
37 firm; provided, however, that any person who has passed the Uniform Certified Public
38 Accountant Examination and holds a valid certified public accountant certificate issued by any
39 other state prior to December 31, 2024 shall be deemed exempt from the education requirements
40 in subsection (e) of section 87A1/2. Any person who qualifies for the practice privilege pursuant
41 to this subsection may exercise such privilege in the commonwealth, without limitation on the
42 period of time within which such person may so practice in the commonwealth as long as such
43 person remains qualified pursuant to this subsection, and shall not be required to obtain a
44 certificate or license pursuant to this section, except as provided in this subsection, submit any
45 other notice to the board or obtain a temporary practice permit from, or pay any fee to the board.
46 SECTION 4. Sections 1 and 2 shall take effect on January 1, 2026.
47 SECTION 5. Except as otherwise specified, this act shall take effect upon its passage.
